§IL Defecere. A summary account is here given of the defections of the following years. Central Italy remained for the most'part constant to Rome, except her old rivale of Samnium, while the alien peoples fell away.

Atellani. Known chiefly in connection with the sabulae Atellanae of which L. speaks v11. 2. 10 in his sketch of the early comedy of Italy.
